reviews.text: A small noodle shop serving Cantonese style noodles. The seating was generally comfortable. The food served are of good standard. There are also a variety of choices. Prices are reasonable comparing to the location and the food served. A place for a quick bite.
Very chewy and springy noodles. Fantastic wontons.

It is a great place to try out for a local Hong kong style restaurant! The food was okay and the price was okay too. Some dishes have an option to choose either a large or small bowl. My friend ordered a small bowl for dinner because we've experienced that dishes are very large size back on our campus and we could'nt finish them but surprisingly the small bowl is a relatively small. There is not much to bite, maybe 5 to 7 mouth fulls so if you want to fulfill your stomach I'd recommend to go for a large which is only a few dollars more. 
Also, the staff struggled to understand english and with my broken chinese the conversation between me and the till lady wasn't pleasant.
good noodle shop of Wan Tung

Good old school local congee and noodle shop. They only serve a few dishes but they have become experts at making the noodles and congee, part of a staple diet for a local. Place is clean and has an English menu for tourist too. Recommended dish on the menu is the pork knuckle noodle (lo mein).

reviews.text: 搬了新位置撈面還是以前古早味多些😉
麵爽口彈牙,湯底鮮甜有大地魚香味, 雲吞屬舊式傳統味道豬肉&鮮蝦平分秋色, 水餃意外地好味係加分區,餡內除有木耳絲更有筍絲。
蠔油撈麵好食，自家麵麵好彈口，冇梘水味，正。
42塊牛肉粥真的好好吃，但就是偏貴，小小小碗！

result.adr_address: 18號 Fa Yuen St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 18號 Fa Yuen St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Good Hope Noodle

reviews.text: Food wise excellent.. Best beef noodle I've tasted.... congee was good too and price reasonable.. But their staff's attitude suck, except the ever smiling cashier!

We dropped in without much of expectation. We ordered 3 dishes: congee pork ball, wonton noodles and dried noodles with stew beef briskets. All are delicious and impressive. Too delicious and forgot to take picture.
Decent noodles, but they're the typical thin flavorless Cantonese noodles. The beef and pork was flavorful and the seasonal veggies were good, though.

Many selections of toppings to go with them noodles. Dry / soup on the side, or comes in soup. Soup is flavorful, you can taste the use of grilled fish in it. Noodles are chewy and thin. Service as usual in HK are brisk and efficient.

I went to this place having read the reviews but found it average. The noodles, the broth, the wonton and the way they cooked greens were all fine but nothing outstanding. Appreciated the flavour of sesame oil which I guess you don't always come across with wonton noodles but wasn't enough to make it particularly great. If you're in the area and you want somewhere easy to eat then it's a safe option. But I wouldn't go out of my way to go back.

reviews.text: 미쉐린 가이드 빕 구르망에 선정된 곳이다. 완탕면의 면의 식감이 특이하지만 한 두번 먹다보면 정말 맛있고 양 또한 많다. 완탕면에서 새우 완자의 양도 많고 소고기 국수의 경우 국물 맛과 고기의 식감 또한 뛰어나다. 소고기 국수(우육면?)과 새우완탕면은 정말 강력 추천. 가격 또한 저렴해 다양한 메뉴를 시켜서 먹으면 좋을듯.
Food wise excellent.. Best beef noodle I've tasted.... congee was good too and price reasonable.. But their staff's attitude suck, except the ever smiling cashier!
炸醬麵保持水準，但感覺味精較重手
